pal <- brewer.pal(8,"Dark2")
  • Function
"report" <- function(file,query,subject){
  suppressWarnings(blt <- readBlast(file=file,
                                    format = BM8ext,plot = FALSE,bestHit = TRUE,
                                    ignoreSelf = TRUE,verbose=FALSE))
  
  plot(density(blt$blf$percent.identity),
       main=paste(query,"mRNA aligned to the",subject),
       sub="percent identity",col=pal[1],lwd=2)
  
  comparisonplot(blt$df$query.cum.cov,blt$df$subject.cum.cov,
                 xlab=query,ylab=subject,
                 main="reciprocal cumulative coverage")
  
  return(list(r7=blt$df$query.id[blt$df$query.cum.cov >= 0.7 & blt$df$subject.cum.cov >= 0.7],
           r3=blt$df$query.id[blt$df$query.cum.cov >= 0.3 & blt$df$subject.cum.cov >= 0.3],
           u7=blt$df$query.id[blt$df$subject.cum.cov >= 0.7],
           u3=blt$df$query.id[blt$df$subject.cum.cov >= 0.3]))
}

2 BLAST results

2.1 Potra01

2.1.1 mRNA

  • The percentage identity of the HSPs is quite high

  • But most mRNA have only very partial high homology to nt sequences (in terms of coverage of the mRNA extent)

potra01.mRNA <- report("nt_Potra01-Potr-specific-mRNA.blt",
               "Potra01","NCBI nt")

A brief Summary

  • Number of reciprocal hits with >= 70% coverage
length(potra01.mRNA$r7)
## [1] 19
  • Number of reciprocal hits with >= 30% coverage
length(potra01.mRNA$r3)
## [1] 37
  • Number of mRNA with >= 70% coverage
length(potra01.mRNA$u7)
## [1] 26
  • Number of mRNA hits with >= 30% coverage
length(potra01.mRNA$u3)
## [1] 37

2.1.2 protein

  • The percentage identity of the protein is quite high, around 50%.

  • But as previously, most protein have high homology to a limited extent of the protein length, albeit almost all the query protein have a full match

potra01.protein <- report("uniref90_Potra01-Potr-specific-protein.blt",
                       "Potra01","UniRef90")

A brief Summary

  • Number of reciprocal hits with >= 70% coverage
length(potra01.protein$r7)
## [1] 45
  • Number of reciprocal hits with >= 30% coverage
length(potra01.protein$r3)
## [1] 79
  • Number of mRNA with >= 70% coverage
length(potra01.protein$u7)
## [1] 46
  • Number of mRNA hits with >= 30% coverage
length(potra01.protein$u3)
## [1] 79
